# FEATURES SUPPORT
				            Linux/WSL	Windows
GPU support                 X		    X
Interactive visualization	X		
Video recording			    X		    X
Environments:
Classic control             X		    X
Box2D                       X		    X
ToyText                     X		    X
MuJoCo                      X
Atari                       X           X

# Create a rl directory, move there and download the compose.yaml file from github
# It may be necessary to use 'sudo' in the docker commands

# USE THE CONTAINER
# Starting the Linux/WSL CPU-only container:
docker compose up linux-cpu -d

# Starting the Linux/WSL GPU-enabled container:
docker compose up linux-gpu -d

# Starting the Windows CPU-only container:
docker compose up windows-cpu -d

# Starting the Windows GPU-enabled container:
docker compose up windows-gpu -d

# Open a terminal session over the container
# (multiple terminal sessions maybe opened on the same container for starting tensorboard or parallel trainings)
docker exec -it rltrain /bin/bash

# For stopping the container before shutting down the computer
docker stop rltrain

---------------
START TENSORBOARD:
tensorboard --logdir logs --bind_all


ADDITIONAL INSTRUCTIONS FOR CUSTOMIZATION
-------------------------
# To build the image from the GitHub repository
docker build -f deustorl-base3.Dockerfile -t inakivazquez/deustorl:base3 .
--------------

# STARTING WITHOUT DOCKER COMPOSE
# For GPU + Mujoco support in Linux/Windows(from WSL-Ubuntu) using network mode host
docker container create --name rltrain --privileged --network host -it --gpus all -v .:/home/rl/my_scripts -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY -e SDL_VIDEODRIVER=x11 -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix inakivazquez/deustorl:base3

docker start rltrain
docker exec -it rltrain /bin/bash

-------------------------
WINDOWS, soporte GUI:
https://ubuntu.com/tutorials/install-ubuntu-on-wsl2-on-windows-11-with-gui-support#1-overview
Instalar WSL para Windows 11
Instalar Ubuntu sobre WSL:
wsl --install Ubuntu

-------------
GPU CUDA SUPPORT, installation instructions:
https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-11-8-0-download-archive

# DOWNLOAD AND INSTALLING THE CONTAINER IMAGE ON YOUR COMPUTER
docker pull inakivazquez/deustorl:base3

-----------------
# Version with no network mode host and explicit port mapping. Ports 2000-2002 is for X server forwarding, port 6006 is for tensorboard forwarding
docker container create --name rltrain --privileged -it --gpus all -v .:/home/rl/my_scripts -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY -e SDL_VIDEODRIVER=x11 -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix -p 2000-2002:2000-2002 -p 6006:6006 inakivazquez/deustorl:base3

